Example animal encounters (taggings, strandings and others)

Source: R/data.R
animals.Rd

A parsed wastd_api_response with 10 animal encounters from get_wastd("animal-encounters")

animals

Format

An object of class tbl_df (inherits from tbl, data.frame) with 3 rows and 41 columns.

Source

https://strandings.dpaw.wa.gov.au/api/1/animal-encounters/?taxon=Cheloniidae&format=json

  • area_name <chr>

  • area_type <chr>

  • area_id <int>

  • site_name <chr>

  • site_type <chr>

  • site_id <int>

  • datetime <dttm>

  • longitude <chr>

  • latitude <chr>

  • crs <chr>

  • location_accuracy <dbl>

  • date <date>

  • name <chr>

  • species <chr>

  • health <chr>

  • sex <chr>

  • behaviour <chr>

  • habitat <chr>

  • activity <chr>

  • nesting_event <chr>

  • checked_for_injuries <chr>

  • scanned_for_pit_tags <chr>

  • checked_for_flipper_tags <chr>

  • cause_of_death <chr>

  • cause_of_death_confidence <chr>

  • absolute_admin_url <chr>

  • obs <list>

  • source <chr>

  • source_id <chr>

  • encounter_type <chr>

  • status <chr>
